snippet.textDisplay: I have a wii U. It was a pretty great system and it is well built. Nintendo just really screwed the marketing up for it. I think most people didn't even know it was not just some accessory for the original Wii for several months AFTER it was released. The Switch (I have one of those too) is definitely a better system but it's build quality is kind of crap. It runs way too hot for its own good, the screen can be scratched just by putting it on it's charging dock, the joycons almost always drift (which can be fixed but still) and the game cartridges actually rattle if you shake them.
